description:
As a Real Estate Professional specializing in the Phoenix and surrounding communities, I have seen a tremendous amount of change and growth here in the Valley of the Sun.  Whether you are new to the market, a seasoned investor, or just trying to sell your home, I have the business expertise and resources to help you attain your real estate objectives.  My established track record includes proven experience in representing the concerns of homebuyers as well as helping buyers and sellers pursue short sale and foreclosure opportunities.  

With the complexities of short sales it is important to have a Real Estate Professional that can provide aggressive representation in this current market.  And while short sales and foreclosures are not for the faint of heart, I have the experience and training that can help buyers and sellers maneuver the challenges of closing short sales and foreclosures.  I am not only familiar with the process, but have direct experience related to bank-owned properties and trustee sales.
  
My certifications include both the Accredited Buyer Representative (ABR®) designation and Short Sales and Foreclosure Resource Program (SFR®); the only short-sale certification approved by the National Association of Realtors®.  I also hold the e-Pro® designation which is a symbol of being able to meet the online needs of today’s Internet savvy homebuyers.  

In addition, I serve as a technical leader in the industry by providing my professional expertise as an appointed Real Estate Special Commissioner to the Superior Court of Arizona.  

I feel it is important to listen carefully to my clients needs in order to fully understand their real estate goals, enabling me to help create solutions and guidance that make sense. I can provide solid real estate direction, accurate property evaluations, and proven market strategies backed by client education and open communication. 

I grew up in Phoenix area and graduated from Arizona State University with as B.S. in Global Business focusing on leadership management.  I have spent my life seeing it change into to community in which it is today.  I am proud to be a part of the continued change. When not working, I enjoy spending time outdoors, traveling, and hiking the Arizona desert. I currently reside in the north valley with my wife and cats.  

With my extensive knowledge of the valley and close ties to the local community; I am dedicated to providing you with the best results and service in the industry.

description:
The Laughton Team with My Home Group has built one of the most successful real estate teams in the Nation, and currently ranks in the top 1% of all real estate teams in the United States. The multi-location team was established in 2007 in Peoria, AZ and has aided thousands of families in the process of buying or selling a home. The team believes homeownership is one of the greatest investments and biggest blessings an individual may ever experience. 

Their success comes from building strong client relationships through honesty and transparency, rather than focusing only on transactions, The Core Values of the Laughton Team are Integrity, Solutions Based, Pursuit of Excellence, Seeking to Understand and being Collaborative.

description: Enjoy privileged access to our Private Client Services, benefits, and opportunities. Frank Aazami, a distinguished entrepreneur, with the provability to plan, negotiate, and grow investments. Master in marketing, real estate, and business development. I am dedicated to providing the highest level of service. My commitment has gone beyond the old standard of customer satisfaction to a new standard of customer delight, exceeding every expectation and in the process establishing a lifelong relationship. I am dedicated to identify and effectively define my clients' needs and goals, then help them achieve those goals through implementing a creative and constructive marketing plan and using my negotiating tactics for their benefit. I tailor a customized "concierge" service for my clients from the beginning stages of a transaction through closing and beyond. I am an inspired member of the National Association of Realtors and proud leader of Frank Aazami - Private Client Group reputation for excellence.

description: Adrea France brings more than 15 years of Real Estate experience to the table. In that span of time, she has accumulated an unparalleled level of varied expertise in title and escrow, mortgage lending, investing and sales. She also has accumulated valuable experience and know-how working as both a Real Estate Sales Agent and as a closing coordinator for a successful Arizona Wholesale Real Estate Investor. Adrea considers the secret to her success to be the high premium she places on concepts such as honesty, integrity, and solid understanding of the industry. She is an Arizona State alumnus, wife and active mom of 2 children.

description: I've been in the Real Estate business since 1977 and have seen the boom and bust from both sides.  Experience in a number of facets of the business from Property Management to Land Acquisitions, REO Management at a Savings & Loan, new home sales in subdivisions, and of course, all forms of residential resales.  You can put my experience to work for you if you plan to buy or sell property.  Finding out what clients need and helping them get it is more than just a slogan . . it's how I do business

description:
“I enjoy knowing that I’ve helped my clients understand all the nuances and parameters of the market. I also enjoy being able to provide them with all the information they need to make an educated decision. They always know that, no matter what, I am looking out for their best interests.”Christopher Karas, REALTOR®Russ Lyon Sotheby’s | International Realty  

Expert in Luxury Real Estate

An expert in the luxury real estate arena, Christopher Karas specializes in the high-end residential market in Paradise Valley, Scottsdale and the Biltmore and Arcadia areas of Phoenix. He has a personal and professional passion for real estate, a passion sparked by his experiences in the industry at the beginning of his career. “After investing in real estate for a number of years and finding it to be a fulfilling and rewarding experience, I wanted to help others enjoy similar emotional and financial rewards,” explains Karas. He adds that nothing in his professional life makes him happier than helping people make the right decision regarding what is often their single largest asset. “It’s truly a thrill to complete a deal with someone that fulfills their particular lifestyle or economic needs.” 

Well-Known and Well-Respected

Karas is well-known and well-respected among his colleagues and peers, a number of whom describe him as filled with integrity, honesty, energy and on-point market knowledge. “I use these attributes to benefit my clients, because as cliché as it may sound, I really do believe in treating them as I would want to be treated,” he says. “I also believe that I owe it to them to substantiate my suggestions with facts, not just opinion. In addition, I listen not just to what is being said, but also to what is not said. I am not only a real estate agent, but also a consultant, market analyst and a friend during what can sometimes be a stressful time in someone’s life.” Karas is proud of his affiliation with Russ Lyon | Sotheby’s International Realty for a number of reasons, including the fact that the firm offers clients access to a wealth of worldwide marketing clout. “This team does things right the first time, whether it is utilizing cutting-edge marketing techniques, sophisticated technology or the most sought-after consultants,” he notes. “Sotheby’s International Realty worldwide tools allow me to effectively reach a very strategic audience and the company brings a highly-respected, quality presence to the luxury market, one that is of great benefit to my clients.”

 Involved in the Community

Karas is originally from Chicago, IL and moved to Scottsdale 22 years ago. He is a graduate of the University of Arizona, and he and his wife Jennifer are active members of Paradise Valley and Scottsdale’s civic and philanthropic communities. Karas is also a current member of the Scottsdale Active 20/30 Club, a non-profit Club that draws the community together to raise funds for and to educate people about the financial, medical and emotional needs of Arizona's children. He currently serves as the Nite Flite Chair of the Club’s gala, one of the organization’s largest fundraisers.

description:
A real estate broker operating in the sprawling Phoenix Metropolitan area since 2013. He graduated from Babson College with a Bachelor of Science Degree in Entrepreneurship, giving him knowledge that was vital in helping set up his successful Realtor practice. David offers real estate services in multiple states, but specializes in the Phoenix area due to his comprehensive knowledge of the city and housing market.

As a member of Russ Lyon | Sotheby's International Realty and Gibson | Sotheby's International Realty, David has developed white-glove skills to cater to high-end clients. He has demonstrated his innate talent for realty once again by successfully handling complex and intricate luxury real estate market. His professionalism, immaculate manners and crisp charm has made him a favorite of the highest echelons in the city.

David maintains and enjoys a healthy lifestyle - either at the gym, the great outdoors and hiking the endless trails that Arizona has to offer.

description: Josie Pakula has lived in the Valley of the Sun since 1997, and possesses extensive knowledge of this community. She is originally from Chicago and studied at the University of Illinois where she earned her Master Degrees in both Nursing and Business Administration in addition to being a U.S. Army Veteran. She even earned her Airborne Wings while on Active duty! Josie quickly established herself as a force in the real estate industry upon becoming licensed in 2010, earning recognition for her incredible work ethic, her exquisite attention to detail, her extensive industry knowledge, and her client-centered approach. She has a history of award winning sales success as her many positive testimonials outline and was honored with the prestigious â€�Top 16 Women in Scottsdale Real Estate in 2016â€³ award. Josie owns her own horses, and supports her two daughters in competitive horsemanship. Her long-term connections within the horse industry and intimate knowledge of the horse lovers world have enabled Josie to build her niche in Horse Properties as well as the Luxury Home Market. Josie serves as one of the most productive and respected Realtors in our Valleyâ€™s dynamic market. She believes in old fashioned values of hard work, integrity, market knowledge and putting her clientsâ€™ goals and needs as job #1. Her valuable insight when bringing buyers and sellers together always results in a successful close. More importantly, Josie has built an impressive team of agents that serve as her incredible support. They are the unmistakable choice to represent your Luxury Home or Horse Property real estate needs. With professionalism, dedication and an extensive book of buyers at their disposal,a property entrusted to Josie is as good as sold. Josie is a true star of the real estate industry, especially when it comes to buying and selling properties. With impressive sales that put her in the top 1% of all agents nationwide and invitation-only membership in some of the industryâ€™s most prestigious organizations. She has consistently earned praise, acclaim, and recognition for the excellent results she achieves for her clients. Josie has in-depth knowledge of the Luxury Home & Horse Property Market: Pricing trends and inventory, together with her comprehensive understanding of the inner workings of the industry and her ability to balance personal one-on-one service with the latest technology and team support, has made her one of the most in-demand Realtor in the business. She is regularly lauded for her extensive marketing efforts, which give her sellers a tremendous edge through a broad National and International presence. Each of Josieâ€™s clients benefit from her affiliation with numerous elite equestrian networking groups, which broadens their scope of recognition and gives them representation of buyers and sellers in the purchase and sale of their property.

description:
Rick Metcalfe first purchased a vacation home in Phoenix many years ago. After 7 years of enjoying the perfect winter weather conditions, he moved his family from the ice and snow of Edmonton, Alberta, Canada to Arizona permanently and has called the Valley of the Sun home for over 20 years.

In Canada, he was in the commercial refrigeration and equipment business for his entire career where he earned the distinction of owning one of the “Top 100 Fastest Growing Companies” in the Canada in 1993. He brought that drive and determination to Phoenix where he purchased a spa and hot tub manufacturing company. After nearly a decade of hard work and a creative approach to marketing, he successfully developed this company into a dominating force in the manufacturing and sales of spas in the state.

In 2003, he successfully sold the spa factory and retired, for what his sons claim, was a mere 24 hours. With his sons Scott and Cory, they immediately began fixing and flipping homes for fun and profit. As their reputation evolved, each of them became Realtors® and that is when CANAM Realty began.. This business experience and background has been invaluable to many of his clients knowing he has the ability to comprehend and negotiate around almost any challenge thrown his way. His expertise has saved or made his clients many thousands of dollars when purchasing or selling a home. The majority of his clients are referred from an extensive base of satisfied customers making Rick one of the most successful Phoenix real estate agents today. He is consistently in the Top 100 of the over 30,000 Realtors® in the greater Phoenix area and would be proud to represent you in your real estate related endeavors.

On the personal side Rick has been a dedicated athlete his entire life and participant in any sport that came available over the decades. His adventurous demeanor has taken him scuba diving around the world, helicopter skiing in the Rocky Mountains, and golfing on every patch of green he can find in Arizona. He has played and coached almost every sport available in North America. He played competitive hockey until the ripe old age of 52 and coached many championship teams in Canada and even the local Mountain Point high school hockey team to the city and state champion ships.

description:
Leo, born and raised in Saginaw, Michigan, was a four year starter in football at Saginaw Valley State University.  After graduating with a bachelor degree in Business Administration and Marketing he moved to Las Vegas and eventually Phoenix which he has called home since 2005.
Leo began his real estate career in 2004 in the state of Nevada.  After moving to Phoenix in 2005 his career has encompassed many different arenas in the real estate space.  He owned and operated a real estate portfolio which he was responsible for 200+ single family home transactions throughout Maricopa County.  After the real estate downturn in 2007, Leo assisted in brokerage operations for one of the largest REO brokerages before buying a construction and development company.  
Leo has a great work ethic but has built long lasting relationships with the foundations of: Honesty, Integrity and Customer Service.  Leo has a passion for helping people with real estate services and even greater love for his two boys, Jack and Anthony.  
Whether buying or selling, Leo is a great choice to handle your real estate needs!
